description: Union home and cooperation minister Amit Shah announced the launch of 10,000 new Multipurpose Primary Agriculture Credit Societies (M-PACS) aimed at bolstering agricultural infrastructure and efficiency. The government's vision includes forming 2 lakh such societies within five years, providing essential resources and financial inclusion for farmers, while modernizing PACs to generate employment for women and youth.
title: Shah launches 10k multipurpose co-ops, eyes 2 lakh target before-time

description: The Chhattisgarh government canceled the police recruitment exam in Rajnandgaon district following allegations of irregularities. This decision came after constable Anil Ratnakar, one of the suspects, died by suicide, alleging that lower-ranked officers were blamed while seniors were protected. Six people were arrested for manipulating exam scores.
title: Chhattisgarh calls off police exam after constable suicide

description: The Enforcement Directorate will challenge a Supreme Court order halting investigations against Santiago Martin and preventing access to digital devices seized from his employees. The SC order also pauses all probes and summons related to Martin, a major political donor, pending further hearing.
title: ED to contest SC freeze on probe against lottery king

description: The government of India is proposing amendments to curb the unauthorized use of the national emblem and names and photographs of the President and Prime Minister, with fines up to Rs 5 lakh and possible jail terms.
title: Centre proposes steep fines, jail terms to curb misuse of national emblem

description: The Railways has modified AC sleeper trains and a Vande Bharat train for the Jammu-Kashmir route to handle harsh weather. Security checks akin to airports will be implemented. Trial runs on the Katra-Reasi section have been successful, indicating readiness. PM Modi might inaugurate both the train service and the Z Morh tunnel soon.
title: Trains to Kashmir may begin rolling next month

description: The death toll from the LPG tanker accident on Jaipur-Ajmer national highway increased to 18, following the deaths of three additional burn victims, including a BEd student and two truck drivers. Fourteen patients remain in treatment at SMS Hospital, with one person being discharged.
title: Rajasthan LPG tanker accident toll hits 18
HC scraps 45-year-old criminal case, Karnataka's oldest

description: A special NIA court in Bengaluru has sentenced Dr Syed Ismail Afaq to life imprisonment and two associates, Abdul Sabur and Saddam Hussain, to 10 years in jail for planning terror activities, including serial blasts ahead of US president Barack Obama's 2015 visit. Convicts are from Bhatkal, Karnataka, and were arrested by CCB sleuths.
title: Bhatkal doctor gets life term for terror plot before 2015 Obama visit

description: Punjab and Haryana HC has ordered a disability pension for the legal heirs of a soldier discharged due to neurosis from recurring nightmares after his lover's suicide. The soldier, invalided out in 1979, had moved HC in 2020 and passed away in 2021. Military authorities are directed to release benefits within three months.
title: High court comes to aid of ex-soldier's kin, grants disability pension

description: Allu Arjun's father, Allu Arvind, donated Rs 2 crore to Sritej, an eight-year-old injured in a stampede at Sandhya Theatre. Contributions include donations from Allu Arjun, Pushpa 2 producers, and director Sukumar. Sritej's recovery is progressing well, and the funds will aid his education and well-being. A meeting with Telangana CM is scheduled.
title: Allu Arjun's dad gives 2 crore cheque to boy injured in stampede

description: Three accused in a gang rape case involving a minor have been acquitted by the Pocso court in Gwalior. The survivor failed to identify herself in a video presented in court. Her inconsistency weakened the prosecution's case. The accused had spent over 90 days in jail. The court found no merit in the allegations against the accused.
title: Gang rape survivor fails to identify self in clip, 3 acquitted

description: President Droupadi Murmu, PM Narendra Modi, and other dignitaries honored former PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee on his birth centenary at 'Sadaiv Atal'. Tributes highlighted his influence on Indian politics and governance, emphasizing his dedication to good governance and public welfare.
title: President , PM Modi lead nation in paying tribute to Atal on 100th birth anniversary

description: Supriya Sule, NCP(SP) senior functionary, stated she cannot fault EVMs without concrete evidence. Despite her victories using these machines, she acknowledged other parties, such as BJD and AAP, claiming proof of EVM manipulation. Sule emphasized the need for discussions to uncover the truth, referencing data shared by BJD's Amar Patnaik.
title: Can't blame EVMs without proof, says NCP's Supriya Sule

description: NDA leaders convened at BJP president J P Nadda’s residence to mark the birth centenary of former PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee and discuss political strategies, including the assembly election in Delhi and the 'one nation, one election' proposal. The gathering underscored achievements under PM Narendra Modi’s leadership.
title: NDA leaders in huddle with eye on Delhi polls, hold talks on ONOE

description: Police in Maharashtra arrested four men after a 17-year-old girl, who ran away due to academic pressure, alleged she was raped by them under the guise of offering help. The girl, a NEET aspirant, travelled to four different places where the incidents occurred. The Pocso Act has been invoked against the suspects.
title: NEET aspirant flees hostel in Maha, raped
Iran minister to visit India in January

description: MT Vasudevan Nair, an iconic Malayalam writer known for his impactful novels and screenplays, passed away at 91. He blended lived experiences into his works, leaving a lasting legacy. He also significantly influenced Malayalam cinema and won prestigious awards, including the Jnanpith Award and Padma Bhushan.
title: MT Vasudevan Nair, iconic Malayalam author, passes away

description: The government announced new secretaries, with Arunish Chawla heading the revenue department and Vineet Joshi in charge of higher education. Rachna Shah will oversee the department of personnel and training. Other key appointments include Amit Agrawal as pharmaceuticals secretary and Neelam Shami Rao as textiles secretary. These changes come ahead of the upcoming Union Budget.
title: 5 weeks ahead of Budget, government appoints new revenue secretary

description: PM Narendra Modi criticized the Congress for not recognizing BR Ambedkar's contributions to India's water resource development while highlighting the Ken-Betwa river linking project's benefits, initiated 23 years ago by Atal Behari Vajpayee's government. The project aims to irrigate 8.11 lakh hectares in Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh, improving water supply and supporting Bundelkhand farmers.
title: PM Modi launches Ken-Betwa link project, hails Ambedkar vision

description: A man with a criminal history allegedly filmed and raped an Anna University student, threatening her and her male friend with the footage. The suspect, arrested a day later, had previously been involved in multiple theft and robbery cases, raising concerns about campus security.
title: Student's rape on university campus shocks Chennai, parties bicker

description: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar received a recommendation for the Bharat Ratna from BJP's Giriraj Singh, citing his impressive performance since rejoining the NDA. This unexpected praise highlights the notable improvements in Bihar's governance under Nitish, compared to previous administrations, according to Singh.
title: Giriraj demands Bharat Ratna for Nitish & Naveen, evokes surprise

description: Stephanie McMahon has risen to prominence in WWE, dating several figures both onscreen and offscreen. Her notable relationships include high school sweetheart, a Baseball Player, WWE superstars Test and Kurt Angle, and finally, her real-life husband Triple H. These relationships played substantial roles in WWE storylines and her career evolution.
title: Stephanie McMahon dating history: Exploring onscreen & real-life relationship

description: 46 civilians, mostly women and children, are reported killed in airstrikes by Pakistani jets in Afghanistan's Paktika province. The strikes targeted alleged TTP camps, with Kabul condemning them as barbaric aggression. Relations between Pakistan and Afghanistan are likely to worsen following the incident.
title: Kabul claims Pak airstrikes killed 46 civilians in Afghanistan

description: Netflix's exclusive streaming of NFL matches, including the anticipated Chiefs vs. Steelers game, is off to a disastrous start with significant technical issues even before kickoff. Fans faced audio problems and program interruptions, reminiscent of previous streaming failures. Despite earlier reassurances from Netflix, their handling remains problematic, leading to widespread frustration.
title: Know why NFL on Netflix is disaster in making

description: Indermit Gill, World Bank chief economist, emphasizes India's potential to elevate its growth from 6% to 8% by enhancing efficiency and economic freedom, focusing on quality education, staying open to FDI and trade, and improving women's workforce participation. India's favourable demographics and balanced economy support these prospects.
title: India should seek to push potential growth from 6% to 8%: World Bank chief economist

description: Life in Katra, Jammu, gets disrupted as Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Sangharsh Samiti leads a 72-hour shutdown, protesting the proposed ropeway project. The agitators argue that the project threatens local livelihoods and traditional pilgrimage practices. Despite police intervention and detentions, the strike continues, with support from BJP and Congress factions.
title: Katra ropeway project: Sangarsh Samiti starts 72hr shutdown, 20 protesters detained

description: Leaders of the National Democratic Alliance, including Amit Shah and Chandrababu Naidu, met in Delhi to counter Congress' criticism of Shah's Ambedkar remark. They emphasized good governance and people's welfare, reaffirmed unity in upcoming elections, and discussed Vajpayee's legacy and future strategies.
title: 'Speak in united voice': NDA leaders meet over Congress' Ambedkar attack

description: A Grozny-bound plane with 67 people onboard crashed near Kazakhstan’s Aktau airport, reportedly after a bird collision, resulting in over 30 fatalities. The incident occurred during deviation from its planned route. Survivors received medical treatment and recovery operations continue; a government commission has been formed to investigate.
title: Kazakhstan plane crash: What lead to emergency landing attempt near Aktau

description: Renowned Malayalam writer and filmmaker MT Vasudevan Nair, fondly known as MT, passed away on Wednesday at the age of 91. The literary giant breathed his last at Baby Memorial Hospital in Kozhikode after being under treatment for 11 days following a cardiac arrest. Despite initial reports of improvement on Tuesday, his condition worsened, leading to his demise on Wednesday night.
title: Renowned Malayalam writer-director MT Vasudevan Nair dies at 91

description: On Christmas Day at Goa's Calangute beach, a boat capsized due to rough seas, tragically causing one fatality and injuring two others. Lifeguards quickly rescued the passengers, including a five-year-old girl. The boat was reportedly unbalanced and lacked life jackets for children. Goa Police is investigating the incident while injured passengers received urgent medical care.
title: Tourist boat capsizes off Calangute beach in North Goa; 1 killed

description: Pope Francis, in his Christmas "Urbi et Orbi" message, urged the end of conflicts worldwide, including those in Ukraine, Gaza, and Sudan. Addressing the humanitarian crisis in Gaza, he called for a ceasefire and the release of hostages. Speaking to thousands in St. Peter's Square, the pontiff emphasised the need for dialogue and peace negotiations.
title: Pope Francis appeals for global peace in Christmas address

description: Senior civil servant Arunish Chawla, currently the pharmaceuticals secretary, is appointed as the new revenue secretary. Amit Agrawal will succeed Chawla. Vineet Joshi is selected as the higher education secretary. The reorganisation also includes key shifts like Sanjay Sethi heading the national commission for minorities and Rachna Shah leading the department of personnel and training.
title: Arunish Chawla appointed new revenue secretary

description: Film producer Dil Raju announced a meeting with Telangana CM Revanth Reddy to discuss support for the victims of the Pushpa 2 premiere stampede. Raju visited KIMS Hospital to check on eight-year-old Sri Tej, who is recovering. Actor Allu Arjun and his team provided financial aid, and long-term support plans are being formulated.
title: 'Pushpa 2' stampede: Producer Dil Raju says 'entire film industry' will meet CM

description: India hosts over 73,000 startups with at least one woman director, driven by advances in technology and government support. The Startup India initiative has facilitated growth through streamlined processes, tax benefits, and funding. Innovations in AI, blockchain, and IoT have helped solve both local and global challenges.
title: India now has over 73,000 startups with a woman director: Government

description: At least 17 houses of the Christian Tripura community in Bandarban's Lama upazila were set ablaze on Christmas Eve. The attack targeted the newly rebuilt Tongjhiri Tripura Para homes, leaving residents devastated. Local authorities have initiated relief efforts and investigations, with ongoing disputes over land ownership cited as a potential motive.
title: Houses of Christian Tripura community torched in Bangladesh

description: Former India captain Kapil Dev expressed disappointment over Ravichandran Ashwin's quiet retirement during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, lamenting the lack of a grand farewell. However, Ashwin himself believes grand farewells are inappropriate, emphasizing that his retirement was his own decision and expressing satisfaction with his achievements without any regrets.
title: 'Grand farewells are wrong': Ashwin reacts to Kapil Dev's remark
Azerbaijan Airlines crash: Survivor films dramatic video from inside aircraft

description: With the Boxing Day Test set to commence at the MCG on Thursday, Virat Kohli aims to overcome his inconsistent batting form in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy series. However, his past performances at Melbourne offer hope, with a strong record including a high score of 169 and an average of 52.66.
title: Can struggling Kohli overcome batting blues at MCG?

description: Canada ended the practice of flagpoling for work and study permits at ports of entry, requiring renewals through IRCC instead. This aims to streamline port operations and border enforcement. Limited exemptions apply, with a focus on improving border efficiency and relationships between Canada and the US.
title: Canada ends flagpoling for work and study permits. What it means?
Tourist boat capsizes off Calangute beach in North Goa; 1 killed

description: The Congress party's camaraderie with AAP during the Delhi Lok Sabha polls has turned to rivalry, with Congress leader Ajay Maken criticizing the alliance as a mistake. Maken condemned Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal, describing him as 'Farziwal' for failing to establish the Janlokpal anti-corruption ombudsman and for the plight of Delhi under AAP's rule.
title: Congress says Lok Sabha alliance with AAP in Delhi was 'mistake'

description: A Taliban spokesman reported that Pakistani air strikes in Afghanistan's Paktika province killed 46 people, mostly women and children. The Taliban condemned the attack as 'barbaric' and vowed defense. This strike follows recent tensions and accusations between the Taliban and Pakistan regarding militant activities.
title: Pakistan airstrikes on Afghanistan kill 46; Taliban calls it 'cowardly act'

description: The Department of Telecommunications (DoT) is raising awareness about fake calls and fraudulent communications, advising citizens on how to report scams. They suggest filing police complaints, calling 1930, and reporting incidents on the Sanchar Saathi portal. Telecom operators have been instructed to play cybercrime awareness messages 8-10 times daily for three months to educate the public on common scams.
title: DoT has ‘fake scam calls’ warning for users: How and where to report fraud

description: Luigi Mangione, accused of murdering UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, sparked a fashion sensation with his burgundy sweater during his court appearance. Social media quickly sold out the $89.50 Nordstrom sweater, likened to infamous outfits of past high-profile trials. Experts warn against glamorising accused criminals, as his 'hot assassin' look garners unsettling admiration and donations.
title: UnitedHealthcare CEO murder: Sweater worn by Luigi Mangione sells out

description: Critics from the far-right, particularly those aligned with MAGA ideologies, viewed Krishnan as a symbol of Silicon Valley elitism and a proponent of immigration policies that they claim disadvantage American workers. Trump, long associated with a tough stance on immigration, faced accusations of hypocrisy for aligning with a figure perceived to represent globalist ideals.
title: Racist Trump supporters target Indian immigrants

description: A jet crash occurred near Aktau, Kazakhstan, involving 62 passengers and five crew members. Approximately 30 people survived with injuries. The accident was caused by an Embraer-190 plane hitting a flock of birds while attempting an emergency landing. The victims included nationals from Azerbaijan, Russia, Kazakhstan, and Kyrgyzstan. Russian President Putin extended his condolences.
title: Bodycam video gives chilling glimpse of Kazakhstan plane crash site

description: Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy will lead the newly established Department of Government Efficiency under President-elect Trump, aiming to cut federal spending and eliminate waste. Their effort is compared to Mao Zedong’s Cultural Revolution, emphasizing the need to avoid ideological purges, factionalism, and short-term chaos that led to long-term damage in China.
title: Dismantling US 'deep state': What Musk can learn from Mao

description: Indian entrepreneurs Aman Gupta and Anupam Mittal express support for Shark Tank Pakistan, noting the humor in the similarities but emphasizing its potential benefits for Pakistani entrepreneurs. They also highlight the importance of regional economic growth and stability, despite unrealistic business expectations observed.
title: 'It's really funny because …': Shark Tank India reacts to Pak version

description: With the Border-Gavaskar Trophy series tied 1-1, Team India faces tough selection choices for the Boxing Day Test at MCG. The sudden retirement of Ravichandran Ashwin creates a void, with Tanush Kotian stepping in. Debate revolves around Nitish Kumar Reddy's place, while reshuffling the batting order could see Rohit Sharma returning as an opener. Gavaskar advocates for retaining key players.
title: Gavaskar explains why India should not drop Reddy for fourth Test

description: Manipur CM N Biren Singh emphasized the BJP's commitment to unity and peace in the state amidst ethnic violence. He highlighted government efforts to aid internally displaced people and urged calm between communities. Singh asserted that only BJP's dedication to nationalism and social justice could save Manipur, referencing various inclusive projects like the Unity Mall.
title: 'Only BJP can save Manipur,' says CM Biren Singh as state awaits peace

description: Ahead of the Boxing Day Test, Australia seamer Scott Boland reminisced about his six-wicket haul at the MCG during the 2021 Ashes Test, highlighting the perfection of that day. Replacing the injured Josh Hazlewood, Boland gears up for the upcoming match, expressing his dedication to be ready for any opportunity despite the challenges of Test cricket on the body.
title: Scott Boland reveals his choice to bowl during a Test match

description: Former Indian spinner Ravichandran Ashwin decodes Travis Head's technique against Jasprit Bumrah, highlighting his clever use of the crease and stance adjustments. Head's adaptability and fearless stroke play have been pivotal in Australia's performances, especially during the ongoing Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Despite his success, Head's vulnerability against round-the-wicket bowling is noted.
title: Ashwin decodes Head's masterplan against Bumrah and Co.

description: Salman Rushdie's banned book "The Satanic Verses" is now available in limited stock at a Delhi bookstore. The ban, imposed in 1988, ended as the Delhi High Court noted the absence of the notification. Rushdie's controversial novel remains highly debated globally, and its release has reignited discussions on free speech and artistic expression.
title: Banned by Rajiv Gandhi govt, why Rushdie's book is now being sold in India

description: MS Dhoni celebrated Christmas with his family, dressed as Santa Claus. Photos shared by his wife Sakshi captured the festive setting with a decorated tree and gifts. Dhoni remains a cricket legend, being the only captain to win all three ICC trophies and leading Chennai Super Kings to multiple IPL championships. He retired from international cricket in 2020.
title: MS Dhoni dons Santa costume for Christmas celebration at home

description: Arjun Tendulkar reached a significant milestone by completing 50 wickets in his white-ball career during the Vijay Hazare Trophy. Representing Goa, the left-arm pacer has taken 51 wickets in 41 white-ball matches after debuting in T20s for Mumbai in 2021.
title: Arjun Tendulkar reaches landmark in white-ball cricket

description: A man attempted suicide near the Parliament building in New Delhi by setting himself on fire. He has been hospitalized at RML Hospital. Delhi police identified the man as Jitendra from Uttar Pradesh. The incident is suspected to be related to personal enmity. An investigation is ongoing.
title: Man sets himself on fire near Parliament in Delhi; rushed to hospital

description: Hydroponic cannabis valued at 1 crore per kg is increasingly entering Chennai from Thailand. This month, DRI officials at Chennai airport seized 14 kg of this potent ganja. The most recent seizure involved 3.6 kg from a passenger arriving from Bangkok, who was identified as a courier for an international drug syndicate. Authorities are actively tracking key operatives.
title: Hydroponic ganja from Thailand new headache for Chennai airport security

description: Raha Kapoor wins the internet as she says hello to the paparazzi and also gives flying kisses as she arrives for the Kapoor Christmas lunch with her parents Ranbir Kapoor and Alia Bhatt.
title: Raha Kapoor gives flying kisses to paps as she arrives with Ranbir & Alia

description: The three Khans of Bollywood, Shah Rukh Khan, Aamir Khan, and Salman Khan, have long dominated Christmas releases in the Indian film industry. Aamir Khan, with consistent releases like Ghajini and Dangal, solidified his presence while Shah Rukh and Salman have also made significant contributions.
title: The Khans and their Christmas releases: A detailed report

description: On Wednesday, Russia launched a devastating attack on Ukraine's energy infrastructure, deploying over 700 missiles and 100 drones. Ukrainian President Zelenskyy condemned the assault, which hit on Christmas, as 'inhumane.' The strikes worsened power outages and civilian suffering, with fatalities and injuries reported. Ukraine seeks advanced air defense systems from allies to counter the escalating attacks.
title: '70 missiles, 100 drones': Russia launches 'massive attack' on Ukraine

description: India's Jasprit Bumrah reached 904 rating points in the ICC Men's Test Bowling Rankings, equalling Ravichandran Ashwin's record. Travis Head climbed to fourth in Test Batting Rankings after stellar performances. Pat Cummins returned to the top 10 all-rounders, while Heinrich Klaasen and Saim Ayub advanced in the ODI Batting Rankings.
title: Jasprit Bumrah achieves historic ICC Rankings feat

description: The Melbourne Cricket Ground is preparing for the Boxing Day Test between India and Australia, while the absence of Shane Warne, who passed away two years ago, is deeply felt. A stand and statue honor him at the venue, keeping his spirit alive. Warne's close friend, Greg Blewett, reflects on their bond and Warne's enduring legacy.
title: Live life, Warne size: Cricket's ultimate showman

description: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy emphasizes the importance of maintaining a positive attitude for career success, especially for professionals in their twenties. He highlights the need for enthusiasm, concrete actions, and continuous learning to attract mentors and prevent complacency. Jassy's own career path, including his sports involvement, reflects these principles.
title: 'Positive attitude helps greatly in success but… ': Amazon CEO

description: India are poised for an advantage in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy after tying the series 1-1, thanks to Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional performance. Ravi Shastri backs India for the Boxing Day Test and applauds the inclusion of debutant Sam Konstas in Australia's team.
title: India must continue to exploit 'brittle' Australian line-up: Ravi Shastri

description: Actor Allu Arjun has decided to offer Rs 2 crore to the child injured in the Sandhya Theatre stampede during the premier show of 'Pushpa 2'. Allu Arjun, his producers, and the director collectively provided the amount to support the child and his family, with the boy reportedly recovering.
title: Stampede case: Allu Arjun, 'Pushpa 2' team offer Rs 2 crore to injured child

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticized Congress-led governments for delaying development projects and neglecting water conservation, while emphasizing BJP's initiatives like the PM Kisan Samman Nidhi Yojana and river-linking projects. He highlighted the lasting impact of former PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee's vision, particularly in rural development, and praised BJP's governance as trusted by the people.
title: 'Delayed projects by 35-40 years': PM Modi's sharp attack on Congress
At least 3 dead, many injured after bus falls into gorge in Nainital

description: In Sidhi, a man named Arman Khan was arrested after he confessed to digging up the grave of his sister-in-law, Shafirunnisha, over a month after her burial, claiming he saw her in dreams. The incident was reported by Amanat Khan, the deceased's husband. Police took action against Arman for hurting sentiments and violating prohibitory orders.
title: 'Saw her in dreams': MP man digs up sister-in-law's grave, held

description: Two more victims of the LPG tanker fire incident in Jaipur have died, increasing the death toll to 17. The fire occurred due to a collision on December 20. Sixteen others are still hospitalized, with three in critical condition. SMS Hospital confirmed the latest deaths, a male and a female, on Wednesday morning.
title: Jaipur highway crash toll climbs to 17 as 2 more succumb to burns

description: India captain Rohit Sharma hopes to regain form in the upcoming Boxing Day Test against Australia by returning to his opening position. Despite a poor series so far, Rohit looks for inspiration from his previous performances. The article highlights Virender Sehwag's remarkable 195 at MCG in 2003-04 as a significant feat for Indian openers.
title: BGT: How Indian openers have fared in Boxing Day Tests at MCG

description: Delhi Congress president Devendra Yadav, alongside Ajay Maken, launched a booklet criticizing the BJP and AAP governments for unmet promises over the past 11 years. Yadav contrasted this with the progress made during Sheila Dikshit's 15-year tenure, highlighting advancements in infrastructure, environmental protection, and social welfare initiatives for vulnerable communities.
title: 'Mauka-mauka': Congress launches booklet highlighting failures of AAP, BJP in Delhi

description: Security personnel recovered 3.6 kg of explosives beneath a bridge in Churachandpur district, Manipur, during a joint operation by Assam Rifles and Manipur police. The seized items included detonators and other accessories, which were neutralized by a bomb disposal team. Additionally, seven weapons were confiscated from Moljol village, including an M-16 rifle and country-made guns.
title: Security forces seize 3.6 kg explosives planted under Manipur bridge

description: Shiv Sena has pledged support for former cricketer Vinod Kambli, who is receiving treatment in Thane. Deputy Chief Minister Eknath Shinde's OSD, Mangesh Chivate, assured Kambli of a Rs 5 lakh aid from the Shrikant Shinde Foundation. MP Shrikant and Deputy CM Shinde will visit Kambli soon to offer further assistance.
title: Vinod Kambli assured of Rs 5 lakh assistance by Shiv Sena

description: Apple's Senior VP Eddy Cue stated that developing a search engine is not a strategic priority for Apple due to the significant financial and resource investment required, the rapid evolution of search technologies, and the misalignment with Apple's core business areas, including their focus on privacy.
title: Apple VP junks this biggest ‘Google rumour’ about the company with these reasons

description: Jasprit Bumrah's consistent performance in India's Test tours to Australia has been crucial for their historic series wins. On his third tour, Bumrah's 21 wickets in three Tests of the ongoing Border Gavaskar Trophy, averaging 10.90, highlight his dominance. His strike rate of 41.0 outshines bowling legends, showcasing his significant impact in Australia.
title: Bumrah proving bigger threat than Hadlee, Holding in Aus
'BJP is rattled': Kejriwal's response on row over AAP's welfare schemes

description: Boosting India's blue-water combat, the Navy will commission two indigenous warships and a submarine in the coming month, bolstering capabilities to counter China's influence. This includes the AI-enabled destroyer Surat, stealth frigate Nilgiri, and submarine Vagsheer, all equipped with advanced sensors and weaponry for enhanced operational readiness.
title: India to commission 2 frontline warships and a submarine in 2025

description: A passenger plane en route from Baku to Grozny crashed near Kazakhstan’s Aktau airport after requesting an emergency landing. The aircraft belonging to Azerbaijan Airlines was diverted due to heavy fog and circled the airport multiple times before the crash. Initial reports indicate survivors, with emergency personnel responding to the scene.
title: Passenger plane with over 70 on board crashes in Kazakhstan, bursts into flames

description: Police have registered a case after a widely circulated video on social media threatened to spread terror during the Maha Kumbh in 2025, with specific dates mentioned. The video included derogatory remarks against Hinduism and political figures. Authorities stated the case is under investigation at the Cyber Police Station in Pilibhit district.
title: Video on X threatens 'terror' at Maha Kumbh 2025; case registered

description: A 72-hour strike in Katra initiated by pony wallas, shopkeepers, and business owners begins on Wednesday to protest a proposed ropeway project. The Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Sangarsh Samiti organized the bandh to oppose the Rs 250-crore ropeway which aims to assist senior citizens and others in accessing the temple.
title: Vaishno Devi ropeway row: 72-hour Katra bandh announced over Rs 250cr project

description: Sanjeeb Wazed, son of ousted Bangladeshi PM Sheikh Hasina, accuses the interim government led by Muhammad Yunus of using the judiciary to target Awami League leaders through a questionable tribunal. The government seeks Hasina’s extradition for alleged crimes against humanity, while India considers denying the request under their political extradition treaty.
title: 'Political witch hunt': Hasina's son accuses Yunus govt of 'weaponising judiciary'

description: Australia's strategy of selecting fast tracks early in the Border Gavaskar Trophy to disrupt India hasn't entirely worked. Jasprit Bumrah has excelled, keeping India competitive. However, Australia's pace attack has not let Indian batters settle, and they are now eager for the more batting-friendly conditions in Melbourne and Sydney to regain form and support Bumrah's efforts.
title: India have all but foiled Australia's 'smart-scheduling' plan

description: Aam Aadmi Party released an AI-generated video of Arvind Kejriwal as Santa Claus giving welfare schemes. The schemes include monthly monetary support for women, free healthcare for the elderly, and free bus rides. Kejriwal also announced an insurance scheme for auto drivers. These initiatives are promised for the upcoming 2025 Delhi Legislative Assembly election.
title: Watch: AAP shares AI video of 'Santa Kejriwal' handing out welfare gifts

description: Grayson Whitaker, 19, suffers from misophonia, a condition where everyday sounds trigger extreme emotional reactions. It prevents him from enjoying family gatherings like Christmas dinner. Misophonia causes involuntary intense responses, and treatments like therapy and hypnotherapy have yet to provide a cure. Raising awareness can improve understanding and support for those affected.
title: Misophonia: This man never had a Christmas dinner with his family due to this rare condition
Mangione’s grin and Prada-like court attire fuels online obsession amid trial
NYC subway horror: Why no one stopped accused? Bystanders, cop 'ignored' victim
How did astronauts stuck in space ended up with Christmas hats? Nasa responds

description: The Enforcement Directorate is investigating allegations of certain Canadian colleges and Indian entities involved in money laundering and human trafficking. The probe follows the death of an Indian family attempting to cross the Canada-US border. Authorities uncovered a network facilitating illegal immigration under the guise of academic admissions.
title: ED probes Canadian colleges for involvement in trafficking Indians to US

description: Arvind Kejriwal alleges plans to arrest CM Atishi and senior AAP leaders in fake cases before the Delhi elections. He claims two new schemes by the AAP government have rattled BJP. BJP accuses AAP of making false promises and misleading the public. They warned against sharing personal data with AAP.
title: 'Plans to arrest Atishi': Kejriwal reacts to BJP's criticism on welfare schemes

description: Rohit Sharma is expected open for India in the Boxing Day Test against Australia, with KL Rahul moving to No. 3 spot. The team management is considering using two spinners at the Melbourne Cricket Ground, with Washington Sundar partnering Ravindra Jadeja. The Border-Gavaskar Trophy is currently tied at 1-1 after three Tests.
title: Boxing Day Test: Rohit likely to open, KL Rahul at No. 3

description: The boy injured at the Pushpa 2 premiere in Hyderabad has regained consciousness after 20 days. Actor Allu Arjun was questioned by police and later released on bail. Pushpa 2 producers provided financial aid to the victim's family, while Telangana’s chief minister held Allu Arjun responsible for the incident, citing safety concerns.
title: Boy injured in 'Pushpa-2' stampede responds after 20 days
Trump’s call for US control of Greenland prompts Denmark to boost defence

description: With the fourth Test at the MCG crucial for India, decisions hinge on whether to include an extra pacer or spinner, considering pitch conditions and recent team performances. Bumrah’s exceptional form remains vital, but reliance on his support bowlers and overall team performance is critical.
title: Will India make changes to ensure Bumrah gets reinforcement?

description: Santa's sleigh is being tracked across the globe this Christmas, with platforms like Flightradar24, NORAD, and Google providing real-time updates. Santa's journey begins at the International Date Line and passes through various continents, ensuring children worldwide receive their presents despite weather conditions.

description: Virat Kohli and Anushka Sharma were seen walking in Melbourne, with a fan capturing the moment. Kohli, part of India's tour in Australia, had acknowledged Anushka's support after scoring a century in the first Test in Perth. description: Telangana Congress MLA R Bhoopathi Reddy warned actor Allu Arjun against criticizing Chief Minister Revanth Reddy, hinting at a ban on his films in the state. This comes after a stampede at a theatre screening his film led to fatalities, with Allu Arjun denying any wrongful actions.

description: An ambulance transporting the bodies of three terrorists from the Khalistan Zindabad Force, killed in a joint Punjab and Uttar Pradesh Police operation, crashed near Rampur bypass. No casualties were reported. The ambulance was hit by an unknown vehicle. Rampur police arrived at the scene and moved the bodies to another vehicle.

The Taliban condemned the attacks and vowed retaliation. The strikes occur amid rising tensions over militant presence, worsening the humanitarian crisis and potentially straining diplomatic relations.

description: The BJP accuses AAP of aiding illegal Rohingya and Bangladeshi immigrants in Delhi by providing them with official documents to use them as a vote bank. The IMD forecasts denser fog and warns of further visibility issues.

Celebrated for his effective governance, he played a crucial role in India's technological and infrastructural advancements. His leadership is remembered for the Pokhran nuclear tests, pushing for economic growth, and bolstering education. Vajpayee's deep cultural roots and literary contributions continue to inspire.

description: Australia's Travis Head has passed a fitness test to remain in the playing eleven for the Boxing Day Test against India. Captain Pat Cummins confirmed Head's inclusion after he recovered from a quad strain. Opener Sam Konstas will make his international debut, and Scott Boland replaces the injured Josh Hazlewood in the squad for the match at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.

description: The India State of Forest Report 2023 highlights severe degradation of dense evergreen forests in four of Karnataka's 10 Western Ghats districts, including Shivamogga and Belagavi. The report attributes the significant loss of forest cover to rampant encroachment, settlements, and various state government projects.
title: Forest loss in Karnataka’s Western Ghats region alarming: Report

description: An Army vehicle transporting soldiers of the 11 Maratha Light Infantry veered off the road and plunged into a gorge near an advanced post in Poonch, J&K, resulting in the death of five soldiers and critically injuring five others. The accident occurred around 5.40pm as the vehicle was en route to Balnoi along the LoC in Mendhar.
title: 5 soldiers die, as many injured as Army vehicle falls into J&K gorge
